title: (Punk Rock) The Rocky Horror Punk Rock Show
description:
The Rocky Horror Punk Rock Show is an album featuring the soundtrack of the 1975 cult film The Rocky Horror Picture Show as performed by modern punk rock bands. The album was released in 2003 on Springman Records.

1.  "Science Fiction/Double Feature" - Me First and the Gimme Gimmes 
2.  "Dammit, Janet" - Love Equals Death 
3.  "Over at the Frankinstein Place" - Alkaline Trio 
4.  "The Time Warp" - The Groovie Ghoulies 
5.  "Sweet Transvestite" - Apocalypse Hoboken 
6.  "The Sword of Damocles" - The Independents 
7.  "I Can Make You a Man" - Pansy Division 
11. "Hot Patootie (Bless My Soul)" - The Phenomenauts 
12. "I Can Make You A Man (Reprise)" - The Secretions 
13. "Touch-A, Touch-A, Touch Me" - The Chubbies 
14. "Once in a While" - Big D and the Kids Table 
15. "Eddie&#039;s Teddy" - Swingin&#039; Utters 
16. "Planet, Schmanet, Janet" - Tsunami Bomb 
17. "Rose Tint My World/Floor Show" - Luckie Strike 
18. "Fanfare/Don&#039;t Dream It" - Stunt Monkey 
19. "Wild and Untamed Thing" - Gametime 
20. "I&#039;m Going Home" - The Migranes 
21. "Super Heroes" - Ruth&#039;s Hat 
22. "Science Fiction Double Feature (Reprise)" - The Ataris 


This is a must-have for any Rocky Horror fans.  They do the whole soundtrack, and some tracks are really really good.  Some tracks are better than others, but all are great fun.  My favorites include "Planet, Schmanet, Janet" by Tsunami Bomb and "Wild and Untamed Thing" by Gametime.
